Based on SEO best practices and competitor analysis, these additional pages will significantly improve your website's authority and conversion rate:
1. Case Studies / Success Stories Page
Why: Builds trust and provides social proof. Potential clients want to see real results from companies like theirs.
Content Structure:
•	3-5 detailed case studies showing: Challenge → Solution → Results
•	Specific metrics (cost savings, time reduction, revenue increase)
•	Client testimonials with photos/company logos
•	Industry-specific examples (SaaS, Healthcare, E-commerce, etc.)
2. Pricing / Plans Page
Why: Transparency builds trust. Even if you offer custom quotes, showing starting prices or package tiers reduces friction.
Content Structure:
•	3 service tiers: Starter, Growth, Enterprise (or similar)
•	What's included in each tier
•	'Starting at $X' or 'Custom Quote' depending on business model
•	Clear CTA: 'Get Custom Quote' or 'Book Consultation'
3. FAQ Page
Why: Reduces sales friction by answering common objections upfront. Great for SEO—FAQ pages rank well for long-tail queries.
